When to use For,DO, do-while

FOR
==========================================================================
when you know the number of iterations in advance or when iterating over a range of values. It consists of an initialization, a condition, and an update statement. 
The loop body executes as long as the condition is true.

while
=========================================================================

while	Use when you want to repeat the loop body as long as a condition is true. The condition is checked before each iteration.



do-while	
=========================================================================
Use when you want to ensure that the loop body executes at least once, regardless of the condition. The condition is checked after the loop body has executed.
